## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

**Recommended Voice:** Elevated editorial authority — the calm Vogue editor who also knows the inside of a nail salon.

**Tone Characteristics:**
- Declarative, not apologetic — "short almond IS the quiet luxury shape," not "short nails can also look nice"
- Warm authority — expert perspective, never condescending
- Specific over vague — names shapes, finishes, and looks precisely
- Aspirational but attainable — she can do this; nothing here requires a different life

**Language Style:** Use "you" directly. British English. No filler affirmations. No em dashes. Rhythm: short declarative sentences anchored by precise nouns (sheer, taupe, almond, gloss). Avoid: "amazing," "stunning," "gorgeous," "simply," "just." Avoid over-explaining — trust the reader.

**Audience Match:** This reader is 25–45, time-poor, style-aware, and slightly insecure about her short nails but aspirational. She responds to confidence, specificity, and being told she already has what it takes. This voice meets her where she is and brings her up, never down.

